Description: InterTADs is an open-source tool written in R, for integrating 
    multi-omics data (e.g. DNA methylation, expression, mutation) from the same 
    physical source (e.g. patient) taking into account the chromatin c
    onfiguration of the genome, i.e. the topologically associating domains 
    (TADs).
